    notes:
      "## The Caffeine + L-Theanine Pairing — The Classical Use Case\n\nThe most-popularized L-theanine use case is the caffeine pairing. The mechanism rationale:\n\n**Caffeine alone** provides cognitive enhancement (alertness, focus, motivation) but produces:\n- Anxiety / jitteriness in caffeine-sensitive users\n- Excessive sympathetic activation (HR, BP, peripheral vasoconstriction)\n- Post-caffeine crash as plasma levels fall\n- Sleep disruption with later-day dosing\n\n**L-Theanine alone** provides modest calm-focus alpha-wave promotion but lacks caffeine's strong cognitive enhancement signal.\n\n**The combination (typically 100mg caffeine + 200mg L-theanine)** produces:\n- Caffeine's cognitive enhancement\n- Reduced anxiety / jitteriness\n- Smoother arousal curve (less sympathetic over-activation)\n- Attenuated post-caffeine crash\n- Improved subjective experience for caffeine-sensitive users\n\nMultiple RCTs support the combination's distinctive cognitive profile (Owen 2008, Giesbrecht 2010, Haskell 2008). The combination outperforms either component alone for cognitive performance with reduced side-effect burden.\n\n**Practical formulations:**\n- **Pre-formulated combinations** (Smart Caffeine, Performance Lab Stim, etc.) typically deliver 1:2 caffeine:L-theanine\n- **DIY pairing** with separate caffeine pills + L-theanine capsules\n- **Tea** provides natural pairing (green tea ~25mg caffeine + ~25mg L-theanine; matcha higher concentration of both)\n- **Coffee + L-theanine supplement** (most common adult use case) — adds 200mg L-theanine to morning coffee for the smoothing effect\n\n## Beginner Protocol\nL-Theanine 200mg with morning coffee/caffeine source × 1 week. Track: jitteriness reduction, focus quality, anxiety levels, post-caffeine crash. The smoothing effect is usually subjectively distinct — most caffeine-sensitive users notice meaningful improvement.\n\nFor users without caffeine pairing: L-Theanine 200mg AM and 200mg afternoon for general anxiety / focus support.\n\n## Advanced Protocol\n**Cognitive performance protocol:** L-Theanine 200mg + caffeine 100–200mg + Alpha-GPC 300mg + creatine 5g (taken consistently) for daily cognitive optimization.\n\n**Single-event peak performance protocol (presentations, exams, races):** L-Theanine 200mg + caffeine 200mg + Aniracetam 750mg + Alpha-GPC 300mg, all 60–90 minutes before event. The L-theanine modulates over-stimulation from the multi-component stack.\n\n**Anxiety priority protocol:** L-Theanine 200–400mg + magnesium glycinate (foundational) + glycine 3g pre-bed for comprehensive calming foundation. Compatible with SSRIs / SNRIs at standard doses (coordinate with prescriber).\n\n**Comprehensive foundational pillar:** L-Theanine 200mg AM + magnesium triple-form (the magnesium tile) + glycine + omega-3 + foundational micronutrients.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A — oral capsule, tablet, or powder. Powder dissolves in water with mild umami-savory taste. With or without food acceptable. With caffeine: take simultaneously for paired effect.\n\n## Synergies\n**Caffeine:** the classical pairing — 1:2 caffeine:L-theanine ratio standard. **Magnesium:** complementary calming (mineral foundation + amino-acid alpha-wave promotion). **Glycine:** complementary calming via different mechanism. **Aniracetam:** complementary cognitive (AMPA PAM + alpha-wave). **Phenylpiracetam:** L-theanine modulates over-stimulation. **GABA / GABAergic supplements:** complementary inhibitory neurotransmitter pathway.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\n**Hidese 2019 (n=30 anxiety / sleep complaints, 200mg/day × 4 weeks):** anxiety and sleep improvements. **Williams 2020 meta-analysis:** supportive evidence for anxiolytic effects across multiple RCTs. **Owen 2008, Giesbrecht 2010, Haskell 2008** (caffeine + L-theanine cognitive RCTs): cognitive enhancement with reduced side effects vs caffeine alone. **Nobre 2008:** EEG-measured alpha-wave promotion. **Juneja 1999:** foundational alpha-wave / cognitive paper.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism well-characterized — alpha-wave promotion documented via EEG; glutamate / GABA / monoamine modulation established. Clinical evidence: anxiety modulation, cognitive enhancement (particularly with caffeine pairing), and stress response attenuation have meta-analysis support. Long human exposure history via tea consumption establishes excellent safety baseline.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid mechanistic foundation (alpha-wave promotion, glutamate/GABA modulation); RCT evidence in anxiety and cognitive enhancement; well-established caffeine pairing. Anecdote: extensive use in nootropic and biohacking communities; subjective effects often perceptible within 30–60 minutes; the caffeine-smoothing effect is the most subjectively distinct. Decision frame: foundational supplement with strong evidence base; the caffeine pairing is the highest-yield single use case; pairs naturally with magnesium / glycine / nootropic stacks; excellent tolerability and safety margin make empirical trial low-risk for most users.",
